                    h4 About
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Risks
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Step 1
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Step 2
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Summary
              .col-lg-8.col-md-8.col-sm-8.col-xs-8.bhoechie-tab
                .bhoechie-tab-content.active
                  p Jo, an artist who regularly comes to the library to do research about strange and sensitive subject matter on both library computers and her own laptop, is currently researching new forms of biowarfare for an upcoming art project. Jo is combing the library catalog for books and electronic resources available through the library, as well as conducting general web research to find out more information on these topics.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  ol
                    li Because Jo’s project deals with topics that have been associated terrorist activity, the most likely entity interested in accessing their library searches and Web search history are law enforcement and national security agents wishing to protect citizens from terrorists.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p The likelihood of government officials gaining access is not very high, because Jo is already protecting themself by using Tor, a service that allows users to anonymize http requests.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p We also recommend that Jo avoid logging into any websites when conducting research to avoid any companies.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p Info to be protected
                  ul
                    li Personal information (e.g. Name, DOB, SSN)
                    li Library usage
                    li Web search history
                    li Location Information
                  p Who is likely to access info against patron’s will?
                  ul
                    li Government
                    li Law enforcement
                    li Corporations
                  p What patron is doing/should do to keep their info private?
                  ul
                    li Browse via HTTPS
                    li Clear browser history and cookies
                    li Install anti-tracking plug-ins on my browser
                    li Install anti-malware software
                    li Log off library terminal
                    li Use Tor
                    li Don’t log in to my accounts
                    li Use an account not in my real name
                    li Create strong passwords
                    li Visit legitimate sites/avoid fake sites
                    li Use a VPN
    .sara.patron.section
      .container
        .row
          .col-sm-4
            img(src='../imgs/sara.svg')
            h4.text-center Patron 3: Sara
          .col-sm-8
            .col-sm-12.bhoechie-tab-container
              .col-lg-4.col-md-4.col-sm-4.col-xs-4.bhoechie-tab-menu
                .list-group
                  a.list-group-item.active.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 About
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Risks
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Step 1
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Step 2
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Step 3
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Step 4
                  a.list-group-item.text-center(href='#')
                    h4 Summary
              .col-lg-8.col-md-8.col-sm-8.col-xs-8.bhoechie-tab
                .bhoechie-tab-content.active
                  p Sara is leaving a difficult family situation and uses the library computers and wifi to access social media, look for housing, and read the news.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  ol
                    li Because things got really bad at home, she is worried that a particular family member will try to track her down and intimidate, bully, or physically harm her. The likelihood of this happening is high: for the past year, the family has depended on a family plan with their mobile phone provider. During that time, the whole family enabled phone tracking features. In addition, her family regularly shared passwords, making it possible for different members to post social media accounts in the account holder’s name.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p The best recommendation for Sara is to immediately change any account passwords that were formerly shared and set up two-factor authentication on sensitive accounts, such as social media accounts, in order to keep her personal communications to herself.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p She is also advised to open a new cell phone account not connected to her family, since call logs and messages are typically available to the account holder.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p She should also change location settings so that any device that takes pictures does not store and share location information, such as in posted photos, and could consider making her social media pages private.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p As an additional precaution, she could consider using a device lock, to prevent anyone from tampering with her phone.
                .bhoechie-tab-content
                  p Info to be protected
                  ul
                    li Location Information
                    li Email messages
                    li Social media activity
                  p Who is likely to access info against patron’s will?
                  ul
                    li Partner or family member
                  p What patron is doing/should do to keep their info private?
                  ul
                    li Install anti-malware software
                    li Use 2-factor authentication
                    li Set up new cell phone account
                    li Remove location information from posted photos
                    li Use a device lock
                    li Make social media settings private
                    li Create strong passwords
